{
  "texts": [
    "Using sentiment analysis alongside other NLP techniques enables researchers to gain a more in-depth understanding of large data sets such as those created in social media, thus providing further insights into potential implications for public health.Topic modeling is an NLP process that is able to sort textual data (eg, social media data) into different themes or categories of topics using probabilistic algorithms [7,33].",
    "One goal of infodemiology is to explore co-occurrences of different concepts of real-world social media data [5]; this is achieved through topic modeling, which groups text-based data into themes through co-occurrences of words and concepts.",
    "Topic modeling can use large data sets to explore relationships between themes of conversation and changes over time through topic evolution [33].",
    "Topic modeling can also be used to track the evolution of discussions across time, taking snapshots of data at different time points and comparing the sentiment, emotion, or topic analyses at each time point.",
    "Topic modeling has been used to characterize specific areas of health that social media users commonly discuss on social media platforms [34,35], and recently, topic modeling has been the focus of a great deal of research exploring the discourse on the COVID-19 pandemic through news and social media sources [36][37][38]."
  ]
}